\f0\b\fs48 \cf0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
ShopSphere Global Marketplace Analysis\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 A complete analytics workflow for the ShopSphere online marketplace: from raw data to an executive dashboard and statistical analysis of an A/B experiment. Tools used: SQL (SQLite), Tableau Public, and statistical reasoning (Simpson\'92s paradox).\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 Data\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Source: educational dataset 
\f0\b ShopSphere: Global Marketplace Analytics
\f1\b0  (final project for a Data Analytics course).\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Five CSV tables covering the years 2022\'962024: customers (3,000), products (250), orders (~12,300), order_items (~26,000), and marketing (216).\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Products belong to seven categories (Electronics, Clothing, Beauty, Home & Kitchen, Sports, Books, Toys) across five global regions (North America, Europe, Southeast Asia, Latin America, Middle East).\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The database was built from CSV files using SQLite (
\f2\fs26 sqliteonline.com
\f1\fs24  or a local SQLite installation). Tables are linked via 
\f2\fs26 customer_id
\f1\fs24 , 
\f2\fs26 order_id
\f1\fs24 , and 
\f2\fs26 product_id
\f1\fs24 .\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 Project Objective\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Conduct a complete analytical assessment for ShopSphere management to evaluate marketing channel performance, identify the most valuable customers, measure the true profitability of product categories (beyond revenue alone), analyze regional trends, and evaluate the results of a checkout A/B experiment. All findings are supported by SQL analysis and an executive Tableau dashboard.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

