\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 Key Findings\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl0
\fs24 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Paid Search
\f1\b0  receives approximately 
\f0\b 45% of the total marketing budget
\f1\b0 , yet delivers the 
\f0\b lowest ROI (1.0)
\f1\b0  and the 
\f0\b lowest customer LTV ($648)
\f1\b0  among all acquisition channels. Influencer Marketing and Organic Search outperform Paid Search on both metrics.\
\ls7\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Electronics
\f1\b0  generates approximately 
\f0\b 60% of total company revenue
\f1\b0 , but also has the 
\f0\b lowest profit margin (12%)
\f1\b0  and the 
\f0\b highest return rate (16%)
\f1\b0 . This is a classic example of the 
\f0\b "high-volume illusion."
\f1\b0  In contrast, 
\f0\b Beauty
\f1\b0  produces relatively low revenue but achieves a 
\f0\b 55% profit margin
\f1\b0  with a very low return rate, making it a 
\f0\b "hidden gem."
\f1\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The 
\f0\b top 5% of customers (150 out of 3,000)
\f1\b0  generate approximately 
\f0\b 35% of total revenue
\f1\b0 . Customer concentration is significant but does 
\f0\b not
\f1\b0  follow the traditional 80/20 Pareto principle. In this dataset, approximately 
\f0\b 36\'9640% of customers generate 80% of revenue
\f1\b0 .\
\ls7\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The checkout 
\f0\b A/B test
\f1\b0  reveals 
\f0\b Simpson\'92s paradox
\f1\b0 . Overall, Variant B appears slightly better (+2% average order value). However, the segmented analysis shows a 
\f0\b strong positive effect for new customers (+22.8%)
\f1\b0  and a 
\f0\b negative effect for returning customers (-3.2%)
\f1\b0 . Therefore, Variant B should be deployed selectively rather than universally.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 Recommendations\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls8\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Reallocate 
\f0\b 15\'9620 percentage points
\f1\b0  of the marketing budget from Paid Search to Influencer Marketing and Email Marketing, while retaining Paid Search primarily for retargeting campaigns and seasonal peaks (November\'96December).\
\ls8\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Increase investment in the Beauty category as an undervalued high-margin segment, while reviewing the Electronics strategy by investigating return reasons and optimizing the product assortment.\
\ls8\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Replace broad discount campaigns with a loyalty program focused on the top 5% of customers and the broader high-value customer segment.\
\ls8\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Deploy the new checkout (Variant B) 
\f0\b only for new customers
\f1\b0 , while retaining the existing version for returning customers until the cause of the negative effect is identified.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

